*How to make each trial have random outputs?*

All you need to use is a pseudo random number generator. It already exists in Java: [java.util.Random][1]

Any instance of Random can generate integers, floats or double values. It depends what you ask it to do. 

With your probability between 0.1 and 10 it could mean you go with integer values in the range of 1 to 100 and divide by 10. So you could run

    Random generator = new Random();
    float percentage = generator.nextInt(100) / 10.0f;

You could as well use nextFloag() which will produce a value between 0 and 1. This you need to map into your range:

    Random generator = new Random();
    float percentage = generator.nextFloat() * (10f-0.1f) + 0.1f;

If I misinterpreted your ranges just adapt the forumuas accordingly. What you need to be aware of is that the generated numbers are pseudo random. While they look random, the sequence they come in can be repeated. If you want to see this in action, initialize your generator with a seed:

    Random generator = new Random(1234);

After that you should be able to repeatedly get the same values when calling nextInt() or nextFloat(). Such predictability is good for software testing/debugging but bad for encryption. In such cases initialize your random number generator like this:

    Random generator = new SecureRandom();

See also [SecureRandom][2].

Now let&#39;s get a closer look at your code. It seems you are running a loop, and inside the loop you are initializing your random number generator and retrieving one value. Per definition these may be the same. Move the line

    Random random = new Random();

so it is before the loop and gets executed once only. With only one random number generator, this instance will deliver mutliple values and thus can start to distribute them over the possible range.



  [1]: https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/19/docs/api/java.base/java/util/Random.html
  [2]: https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/19/docs/api/java.base/java/security/SecureRandom.html

